Package author: Igor Gaponenko

Please describe any modifications that you made to the package in the
reverse time order.

Tag: V00-01-03
2013-05-09 Andy
- switch to AppUtils.AppBase as base class for python application

Tag: V00-01-02
2011-05-23 Andy
- suppress compilation warning about sscanf format (which could have 
  also been an error) in SciMDTestApp.cpp

Tag: V00-01-00
2009-12-09 Igor Gaponenko
- redesigned the schema to delegate all instrument/experiment specific
requests to a separate database (Experiments registry Database). Use
only a numeric 'exper_id' to identify an experiment. ATTENTION: the new
schema is not compatible with the old one.
- added 'CASCADE' for both 'UPDATE' and "DELETE' in all foreign keys 
- modified the source code accordingly
- modified and simplified the administrative tool (Python)
- extended the C++ API with a method allowing to define run parameters;
added a test for the new method into the C++ test application; modified
the constructor of C++ API class SciMD::Connection to accept separate
ODBC connections for SciMD and RegDB databases.

Tag: V00-00-10
2009-11-16 Igor Gaponenko
- added the interactive command 'remove_runs' (see Python admin tools)

Tag: V00-00-09
2009-10-12 Igor Gaponenko
- fixed a bug in the C++ API

Tag: V00-00-08
2009-10-10 Igor Gaponenko
- added 64-bit integer parameter type to schema
- fixed bugs in the admin tool
- make modifications to both Admin tool and C++ API and its test

Tag: V00-00-07
2009-09-13 Igor Gaponenko
- added missing instrument parameter to the relevant methods of the C++ API

Tag: V00-00-06
2009-05-19 Igor Gaponenko
- migrated to use the new Python Class LusiTime.Time

Tag: V00-00-05
2009-05-19 Igor Gaponenko
- changes in the schema to replace SQL's DATETIME with 64-bit integer (BIGINT)
  to represent timestamps including nanoseconds.
- reinforced API for run types
- improved test application  

Tag: V00-00-00
2008-10-07 Andy Salnikov
- just created this template file, this entry is an example of the change log
  entry
- keep it brief and easy to read
- always include author name and date of the change, provide CVS tag when 
  appropriate

